commits.author: Jungwoo Song
commits.message:
Valkey connector (#1743)

* feat: Add dependency for valkey-glide

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add Valkey adapter

- Using same url prefix(valkey://) supporting standalone and cluster mode
- Use query param for checking mode.
- Standalone mode supports selecting database and cluster mode doesn't support it (but after Valkey 9, it can support database mode)

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Valkey Connector

- Implement valkey connector based on redis connector but using other library, Valkey-GLIDE managed by Valkey organization.
- Use mget and pipeline put at standalone and cluster mode
- Use Hash slot for reducing network latency at cluster mode.
- When tested with 10 keys, Valkey connector is 5 ~ 20% faster at standalone mode and up to 70%(avg 60%+) faster at cluster mode.

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* test: add test for valkey connector

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: add specific version for supporting pipelinig

* fix: linting

* fix: add checking memory equality at test

* feat: Use extra config for simple paramters

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: remove valkey-glide depedency from common.txt

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add try-except and prevent memory leak

- Add try-except under assert statement for checking error
- Add memory_obj.ref_count_down() for preventing memory leak

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: double check for config and extra_config

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: lint

* docs: Add docs for valkey connector

commits.message:
[vLLM][Core]: Add shutdown to vLLM connector (#1945)

* Add shutdown to vLLM connector

The vLLM connector does not shutdown LMCache gracefully. This
commit addsa shutdown method which calls cleanup methods for all
the objects that are created during the startup.

There are also updates to some of the cleanup methods of the objects
themselves to:

- Reduce deadlock and unsafe attribute access
- Add error handling and logging

Changes as follows:

1. `lmcache/integration/vllm/vllm_v1_adapter.py`
   - Added `shutdown()` method
   - Added timeout protection for all cleanup operations
   - Added missing resource cleanup
   - Added comprehensive logging
   - Added error tracking and reporting

2. `lmcache/v1/cache_engine.py`
   - Enhanced `close()` method with comprehensive logging
   - Enhanced `LMCacheEngineBuilder.destroy()` with detailed logging
   - Added error handling for all operations

3. `lmcache/v1/storage_backend/storage_manager.py`
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout protection
   - Added 10-second timeout to thread.join()
   - Added individual backend closure logging
   - Added error handling for event loop stop

4. `lmcache/v1/offload_server/zmq_server.py`
   - Enhanced `process_request()` with exception handling
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout
   - Added graceful thread termination
   - Added detailed logging

5. `lmcache/observability.py`
   - Rewrote `LMCacheStatsLogger.shutdown()` method with timeout protection
   - Added smart timeout calculation (log_interval + 2 seconds, minimum 5s)
   - Added comprehensive logging for stats logger shutdown
   - Added error handling for thread join

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

commits.author: Martin Hickey
commits.message:
[Core][vLLM]: Add KV event generation (#1959)

* Add KV event generation

This commit adds generation of kv events. It creates the events during
LMCache storage operations and stores them in the cache engine.
The vLLM model runner and scheduler processes then handle the events and the events are
finally published by the vLLM scheduler process.

The overall data flow is as follows:
- Model runner process calls `get_kv_connector_stats` which calls cache_engine to return the events
- Model runner process sends the information to the scheduler process via `KVConnectorOutput`
- Scheduler process calls `update_connector_output` and connector gets access to events in scheduler side now
- Scheduler calls `take_events`, and connector returns the latest events to be published bty the scheduler

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Update to use the new kv cache events property in KVConnectorOutput

This commit replaces piggybacking on the stats property.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Fix block hash value

Block hash value should be based on LMCache client key chunk_hash field.
This means it will be sonsistent across workers for the same events as its
only based on token ids.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Rollback changes to lmcache_connector_v1.py

Wait until changes in vLLM merge first before adding the changes
for the connector in LMCache repo. Otherwise, will be constantly
changhing and this needs to merge before vLLM PR.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Update lmcache/v1/cache_engine.py

commits.author: Dongjoo Seo
commits.message:
[hotfix/UT] Prevent cache corruption when vLLM prefix cache overlaps with LMCache (#2207)

* Change save_unfull_chunk default to False and update documentation

* Add save_unfull_chunk parametrization to benchmark tests

- Add parametrization for save_unfull_chunk (False/True) to all benchmark tests
- Update test assertions to handle both chunk-aligned and full token counts
- Fix line length style issues

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count and fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask for save_unfull_chunk

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Parametrize all test_paged_* functions with save_unfull_chunk=[False, True]
- Fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask to handle chunk-aligned mask requirements
  when save_unfull_chunk=True
- Maintain original test flow while supporting both save_unfull_chunk values
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count in test_benchmark.py to module level

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Remove duplicate get_expected_count definitions from test functions
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function with
  save_unfull_chunk and chunk_size parameters
- Improve code maintainability and consistency with test_cache_engine.py

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* config: Auto-enable save_unfull_chunk for PD mode

PD (Peer-to-Peer Disaggregation) requires save_unfull_chunk=True to
ensure complete KV cache transfer from prefill node to decode node.
Without this, partial chunks would be discarded, causing incomplete
KV cache transfer and wrong results on the decode node.

- Automatically set save_unfull_chunk=True when enable_pd=True
- Add warning log when auto-setting save_unfull_chunk
- Add info log when save_unfull_chunk is already True in PD mode
- Ensure PD users get correct configuration without manual intervention

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

---------

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

commits.author: tianlang-wq
commits.message:
[Bugfix] AttributeError when using store-based KV sharing without disagg_spec (missing null check) (#2154)

* [Bugfix] Fix disaggregation token transfer logic for KV producer

This change fixes a potential issue in the disaggregation logic where
the KV producer role might attempt to access request.disagg_spec
without proper validation, which could cause issues when disagg_spec
is None.

Key changes:
- Add additional check to ensure request.disagg_spec exists before
  accessing num_transferred_tokens property
- Prevents potential AttributeError when disagg_spec is None
- Maintains the original logic for calculating skip_leading_tokens
  when disagg_spec is properly configured

This ensures more robust handling of disaggregation scenarios in
the KV cache transfer process.

Signed-off-by:  <dong.peiqi@neolink.com>

* [Bugfix] Add comment for shared storage disaggregation handling

Add explanatory comment to clarify that shared storage disaggregation
will not have a disagg_spec passed in, improving code readability
and maintainability.

Signed-off-by:  <dong.peiqi@neolink.com>

commits.author: Tomer Shmilovich
commits.message:
[Core] Introduce NixlStorageBackend dynamic mode (#2024)

* [Core] Seperate NixlStorageBackend classes

This commit prepares the backend for integration of
DynamicStorageBackend, implemented in the next commit.

Signed-off-by: Tomer Shmilovich <tshmilovich@nvidia.com>

* [Core] Introduce NixlStorageBackend dynamic mode

This commit incorporates PR #1939 into NixlStorageBackend, under the
name of NixlDynamicStorageBackend, in order to prevent having 2 nixl
storage backends as well as lessen code duplication.

In order to use this new dynamic storage mode, which creates object keys
when needed instead of a limited pre-allocated amount,
extra_config.nixl_pool_size should be set to 0.

This mode is currently only supported for nixl OBJ backend.

commits.author: Jungwoo Song
commits.message:
Valkey connector (#1743)

* feat: Add dependency for valkey-glide

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add Valkey adapter

- Using same url prefix(valkey://) supporting standalone and cluster mode
- Use query param for checking mode.
- Standalone mode supports selecting database and cluster mode doesn't support it (but after Valkey 9, it can support database mode)

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Valkey Connector

- Implement valkey connector based on redis connector but using other library, Valkey-GLIDE managed by Valkey organization.
- Use mget and pipeline put at standalone and cluster mode
- Use Hash slot for reducing network latency at cluster mode.
- When tested with 10 keys, Valkey connector is 5 ~ 20% faster at standalone mode and up to 70%(avg 60%+) faster at cluster mode.

commits.author: Martin Hickey
commits.message:
[vLLM][Core]: Add shutdown to vLLM connector (#1945)

* Add shutdown to vLLM connector

The vLLM connector does not shutdown LMCache gracefully. This
commit addsa shutdown method which calls cleanup methods for all
the objects that are created during the startup.

There are also updates to some of the cleanup methods of the objects
themselves to:

- Reduce deadlock and unsafe attribute access
- Add error handling and logging

Changes as follows:

1. `lmcache/integration/vllm/vllm_v1_adapter.py`
   - Added `shutdown()` method
   - Added timeout protection for all cleanup operations
   - Added missing resource cleanup
   - Added comprehensive logging
   - Added error tracking and reporting

2. `lmcache/v1/cache_engine.py`
   - Enhanced `close()` method with comprehensive logging
   - Enhanced `LMCacheEngineBuilder.destroy()` with detailed logging
   - Added error handling for all operations

3. `lmcache/v1/storage_backend/storage_manager.py`
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout protection
   - Added 10-second timeout to thread.join()
   - Added individual backend closure logging
   - Added error handling for event loop stop

4. `lmcache/v1/offload_server/zmq_server.py`
   - Enhanced `process_request()` with exception handling
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout
   - Added graceful thread termination
   - Added detailed logging

5. `lmcache/observability.py`
   - Rewrote `LMCacheStatsLogger.shutdown()` method with timeout protection
   - Added smart timeout calculation (log_interval + 2 seconds, minimum 5s)
   - Added comprehensive logging for stats logger shutdown
   - Added error handling for thread join

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

commits.author: maobaolong
commits.message:
[Controller] Refactor heartbeat from PUSH to REQ-REP mode and supply heartbeat command framework (#2251)

[Controller] Refactor heartbeat from PUSH to REQ-REP mode

- HeartbeatMsg now inherits from WorkerReqMsg instead of RegisterMsg
- Added HeartbeatCommandType enum and HeartbeatCommand struct for extensible commands
- HeartbeatRetMsg now uses command pattern instead of need_full_sync field
- Worker heartbeat handler dispatches commands via _handle_heartbeat_command
- Updated registration_controller heartbeat to return HeartbeatCommand
- Updated benchmark heartbeat handler for command-based response

The command abstraction allows controller to send various commands to workers
through the heartbeat mechanism. New commands can be added by extending
HeartbeatCommandType enum without changing the message structure.

Signed-off-by: baoloongmao <baoloongmao@tencent.com>

- Add parametrization for save_unfull_chunk (False/True) to all benchmark tests
- Update test assertions to handle both chunk-aligned and full token counts
- Fix line length style issues

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count and fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask for save_unfull_chunk

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Parametrize all test_paged_* functions with save_unfull_chunk=[False, True]
- Fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask to handle chunk-aligned mask requirements
  when save_unfull_chunk=True
- Maintain original test flow while supporting both save_unfull_chunk values
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count in test_benchmark.py to module level

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Remove duplicate get_expected_count definitions from test functions
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function with
  save_unfull_chunk and chunk_size parameters
- Improve code maintainability and consistency with test_cache_engine.py

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* config: Auto-enable save_unfull_chunk for PD mode

PD (Peer-to-Peer Disaggregation) requires save_unfull_chunk=True to
ensure complete KV cache transfer from prefill node to decode node.
Without this, partial chunks would be discarded, causing incomplete
KV cache transfer and wrong results on the decode node.

- Automatically set save_unfull_chunk=True when enable_pd=True
- Add warning log when auto-setting save_unfull_chunk
- Add info log when save_unfull_chunk is already True in PD mode
- Ensure PD users get correct configuration without manual intervention

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

commits.author: Martin Hickey
commits.message:
[Core][vLLM]: Add KV event generation (#1959)

* Add KV event generation

This commit adds generation of kv events. It creates the events during
LMCache storage operations and stores them in the cache engine.
The vLLM model runner and scheduler processes then handle the events and the events are
finally published by the vLLM scheduler process.

The overall data flow is as follows:
- Model runner process calls `get_kv_connector_stats` which calls cache_engine to return the events
- Model runner process sends the information to the scheduler process via `KVConnectorOutput`
- Scheduler process calls `update_connector_output` and connector gets access to events in scheduler side now
- Scheduler calls `take_events`, and connector returns the latest events to be published bty the scheduler

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Update to use the new kv cache events property in KVConnectorOutput

This commit replaces piggybacking on the stats property.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Fix block hash value

Block hash value should be based on LMCache client key chunk_hash field.
This means it will be sonsistent across workers for the same events as its
only based on token ids.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Rollback changes to lmcache_connector_v1.py

Wait until changes in vLLM merge first before adding the changes
for the connector in LMCache repo. Otherwise, will be constantly
changhing and this needs to merge before vLLM PR.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

commits.author: Tomer Shmilovich
commits.message:
[Core] Introduce NixlStorageBackend dynamic mode (#2024)

This commit prepares the backend for integration of
DynamicStorageBackend, implemented in the next commit.

Signed-off-by: Tomer Shmilovich <tshmilovich@nvidia.com>

* [Core] Introduce NixlStorageBackend dynamic mode

This commit incorporates PR #1939 into NixlStorageBackend, under the
name of NixlDynamicStorageBackend, in order to prevent having 2 nixl
storage backends as well as lessen code duplication.

In order to use this new dynamic storage mode, which creates object keys
when needed instead of a limited pre-allocated amount,
extra_config.nixl_pool_size should be set to 0.

This mode is currently only supported for nixl OBJ backend.

commits.author: tianlang-wq
commits.message:
[Bugfix] AttributeError when using store-based KV sharing without disagg_spec (missing null check) (#2154)

* [Bugfix] Fix disaggregation token transfer logic for KV producer

This change fixes a potential issue in the disaggregation logic where
the KV producer role might attempt to access request.disagg_spec
without proper validation, which could cause issues when disagg_spec
is None.

Key changes:
- Add additional check to ensure request.disagg_spec exists before
  accessing num_transferred_tokens property
- Prevents potential AttributeError when disagg_spec is None
- Maintains the original logic for calculating skip_leading_tokens
  when disagg_spec is properly configured

This ensures more robust handling of disaggregation scenarios in
the KV cache transfer process.

Signed-off-by:  <dong.peiqi@neolink.com>

* [Bugfix] Add comment for shared storage disaggregation handling

Add explanatory comment to clarify that shared storage disaggregation
will not have a disagg_spec passed in, improving code readability
and maintainability.

Signed-off-by: AI Assistant <ai.assistant@example.com>
Signed-off-by:  <dong.peiqi@neolink.com>

commits.author: maobaolong
commits.message:
[Controller] Refactor heartbeat from PUSH to REQ-REP mode and supply heartbeat command framework (#2251)

[Controller] Refactor heartbeat from PUSH to REQ-REP mode

- HeartbeatMsg now inherits from WorkerReqMsg instead of RegisterMsg
- Added HeartbeatCommandType enum and HeartbeatCommand struct for extensible commands
- HeartbeatRetMsg now uses command pattern instead of need_full_sync field
- Worker heartbeat handler dispatches commands via _handle_heartbeat_command
- Updated registration_controller heartbeat to return HeartbeatCommand
- Updated benchmark heartbeat handler for command-based response

The command abstraction allows controller to send various commands to workers
through the heartbeat mechanism. New commands can be added by extending
HeartbeatCommandType enum without changing the message structure.

commits.author: Dongjoo Seo
commits.message:
[hotfix/UT] Prevent cache corruption when vLLM prefix cache overlaps with LMCache (#2207)

* Change save_unfull_chunk default to False and update documentation

* Add save_unfull_chunk parametrization to benchmark tests

- Add parametrization for save_unfull_chunk (False/True) to all benchmark tests
- Update test assertions to handle both chunk-aligned and full token counts
- Fix line length style issues

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count and fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask for save_unfull_chunk

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Parametrize all test_paged_* functions with save_unfull_chunk=[False, True]
- Fix test_paged_store_kv_tensors_mask to handle chunk-aligned mask requirements
  when save_unfull_chunk=True
- Maintain original test flow while supporting both save_unfull_chunk values
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* test: Refactor get_expected_count in test_benchmark.py to module level

- Add module-level get_expected_count helper function to avoid duplication
- Remove duplicate get_expected_count definitions from test functions
- Update all get_expected_count calls to use module-level function with
  save_unfull_chunk and chunk_size parameters
- Improve code maintainability and consistency with test_cache_engine.py

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

* config: Auto-enable save_unfull_chunk for PD mode

PD (Peer-to-Peer Disaggregation) requires save_unfull_chunk=True to
ensure complete KV cache transfer from prefill node to decode node.
Without this, partial chunks would be discarded, causing incomplete
KV cache transfer and wrong results on the decode node.

- Automatically set save_unfull_chunk=True when enable_pd=True
- Add warning log when auto-setting save_unfull_chunk
- Add info log when save_unfull_chunk is already True in PD mode
- Ensure PD users get correct configuration without manual intervention

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

Signed-off-by: Dongjoo Seo <dongjoo.seo1@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: DongDongJu <commisori28@gmail.com>

commits.author: Martin Hickey
commits.message:
[vLLM][Core]: Add shutdown to vLLM connector (#1945)

* Add shutdown to vLLM connector

The vLLM connector does not shutdown LMCache gracefully. This
commit addsa shutdown method which calls cleanup methods for all
the objects that are created during the startup.

There are also updates to some of the cleanup methods of the objects
themselves to:

- Reduce deadlock and unsafe attribute access
- Add error handling and logging

Changes as follows:

1. `lmcache/integration/vllm/vllm_v1_adapter.py`
   - Added `shutdown()` method
   - Added timeout protection for all cleanup operations
   - Added missing resource cleanup
   - Added comprehensive logging
   - Added error tracking and reporting

2. `lmcache/v1/cache_engine.py`
   - Enhanced `close()` method with comprehensive logging
   - Enhanced `LMCacheEngineBuilder.destroy()` with detailed logging
   - Added error handling for all operations

3. `lmcache/v1/storage_backend/storage_manager.py`
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout protection
   - Added 10-second timeout to thread.join()
   - Added individual backend closure logging
   - Added error handling for event loop stop

4. `lmcache/v1/offload_server/zmq_server.py`
   - Enhanced `process_request()` with exception handling
   - Rewrote `close()` method with timeout
   - Added graceful thread termination
   - Added detailed logging

5. `lmcache/observability.py`
   - Rewrote `LMCacheStatsLogger.shutdown()` method with timeout protection
   - Added smart timeout calculation (log_interval + 2 seconds, minimum 5s)
   - Added comprehensive logging for stats logger shutdown
   - Added error handling for thread join

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

commits.author: Martin Hickey
commits.message:
[Core][vLLM]: Add KV event generation (#1959)

* Add KV event generation

This commit adds generation of kv events. It creates the events during
LMCache storage operations and stores them in the cache engine.
The vLLM model runner and scheduler processes then handle the events and the events are
finally published by the vLLM scheduler process.

The overall data flow is as follows:
- Model runner process calls `get_kv_connector_stats` which calls cache_engine to return the events
- Model runner process sends the information to the scheduler process via `KVConnectorOutput`
- Scheduler process calls `update_connector_output` and connector gets access to events in scheduler side now
- Scheduler calls `take_events`, and connector returns the latest events to be published bty the scheduler

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Update to use the new kv cache events property in KVConnectorOutput

This commit replaces piggybacking on the stats property.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Fix block hash value

Block hash value should be based on LMCache client key chunk_hash field.
This means it will be sonsistent across workers for the same events as its
only based on token ids.

Signed-off-by: Martin Hickey <martin.hickey@ie.ibm.com>

* Rollback changes to lmcache_connector_v1.py

Wait until changes in vLLM merge first before adding the changes
for the connector in LMCache repo. Otherwise, will be constantly
changhing and this needs to merge before vLLM PR.

This commit incorporates PR #1939 into NixlStorageBackend, under the

commits.message:
[Bugfix] AttributeError when using store-based KV sharing without disagg_spec (missing null check) (#2154)

* [Bugfix] Fix disaggregation token transfer logic for KV producer

This change fixes a potential issue in the disaggregation logic where
the KV producer role might attempt to access request.disagg_spec
without proper validation, which could cause issues when disagg_spec
is None.

Key changes:
- Add additional check to ensure request.disagg_spec exists before
  accessing num_transferred_tokens property
- Prevents potential AttributeError when disagg_spec is None
- Maintains the original logic for calculating skip_leading_tokens
  when disagg_spec is properly configured

This ensures more robust handling of disaggregation scenarios in
the KV cache transfer process.

will not have a disagg_spec passed in, improving code readability

commits.author: Jungwoo Song
commits.message:
Valkey connector (#1743)

* feat: Add dependency for valkey-glide

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add Valkey adapter

- Using same url prefix(valkey://) supporting standalone and cluster mode
- Use query param for checking mode.
- Standalone mode supports selecting database and cluster mode doesn't support it (but after Valkey 9, it can support database mode)

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Valkey Connector

- Implement valkey connector based on redis connector but using other library, Valkey-GLIDE managed by Valkey organization.
- Use mget and pipeline put at standalone and cluster mode
- Use Hash slot for reducing network latency at cluster mode.
- When tested with 10 keys, Valkey connector is 5 ~ 20% faster at standalone mode and up to 70%(avg 60%+) faster at cluster mode.

commits.message:
[Bugfix] fix duplicate log when enable verbose logging (#2199)

Multiple calls to getLogger() with the same name will always return a
reference to the same Logger object. So when enable verbose logging in
the multi-round-qa or rag benchmark, it will add two handlers, which
results in duplicate log messages.
